Package io.covrsecurity.onyonservice

Class Job

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.covrsecurity.onyonservice.Job
  • public class Job
extends java.lang.Object
    The main work model. This is used to keep and process information for requests sent to the cloud service. This is also stored locally for persistence. Job instances are the main part of a request life cycle.

      • failedJob

        public static Job failedJob​(io.covrsecurity.onyon.RequestType type,
                            StatusCode statusCode,
                            java.lang.String optionalMessage)
        Factory method to quickly build a failed job. Can be used in those places where a job has to be returned, but the operation failed.
        Parameters:
        type - The type of request that should have been handled by the job.
        statusCode - The status code of the job.
        optionalMessage - A message that describes what went wrong, may be null.
        Returns:
        A Job instance that is initialised as failed.

        public void addItem​(java.lang.String data,
                    java.lang.String mimeType,
                    java.lang.String tag)
        Adds an item to the job. Items consist of three parts, some data, a mime type and an identifying tag.
        Parameters:
        data - Some data.
        mimeType - The mime type of data.
        tag - A tag that identifies the item.
